properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore Island VA out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague VA out 20 nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 14 at 2:38PM EST until January 17 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds increasing to 25 to 30 kt with gusts to
35 to 40 kt Thursday, continuing Thursday night. Seas building
to 5 to 7 ft.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm.

* WHEN...From Thursday morning through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
